# 6.2 The Token-Stacking Linter Subsystem
Below is the production-grade linter module designed to ingest messy, wide AI-generated source files. It scans the abstract syntax configuration and programmatically applies multiline stack formatting to ensure complete, fit-to-screen compilation:

```python
import sys

class PanmatrixLinter:
    def __init__(self, limit=45):
        self.limit = limit

    def audit_line(self, line_str):
        """
        Flags line components that violate 
        the screen width baseline metric.
        """
        clean = line_str.rstrip("\n")
        if len(clean) > self.limit:
            return True, clean
        return False, clean

    def split_assignment(self, code_line):
        """
        Refactors assignment matrices 
        by introducing elegant vertical 
        parenthetical stacks.
        """
        if "=" not in code_line:
            return [code_line]
            
        parts = code_line.split("=", 1)
        lhs = parts[0].strip()
        rhs = parts[1].strip()
        
        # Build optimized line segments
        l1 = f"{lhs} = ("
        l2 = f"    {rhs}"
        l3 = ")"
        return [l1, l2, l3]

    def enforce_screen_fit(self, file_path):
        """
        Ingests and reformats source strings 
        to protect mobile screen margins.
        """
        with open(file_path, "r") as f:
            lines = f.readlines()
            
        new_source = []
        for line in lines:
            flagged, text = self.audit_line(line)
            if flagged and "=" in text:
                # Break up long calculations
                chunks = self.split_assignment(text)
                new_source.extend(chunks)
            else:
                new_source.append(text)
                
        # Write clean formatted buffer back
        with open(file_path, "w") as f:
            for item in new_source:
                f.write(f"{item}\n")
                
        print("[+] Screen-fit audit clean.")
```

